Package com.iontrading.mkv.events

Interface MkvRecordListenerExt

  • All Superinterfaces:
    EventListener, MkvRecordListener
    @Keep
@KeepPublicClassMemberNames
public interface MkvRecordListenerExt
extends MkvRecordListener
    Interface used for notifying data updates on records belonging to patterns and persistent sets.

      • onFullUpdate

        void onFullUpdate​(MkvRecord record,
                  MkvSupply supply,
                  boolean isSnapshot)
        Events generated when an update on the subscribed record is received, and all subscribed fields are available. A subscription can fail asynchronously if data entitlements are enabled and the subscriber is not entitled to subscribe a record/pattern; in that case the supply is set to a dummy value and the error code for the MkvRecord is set.
        Specified by:
        onFullUpdate in interface MkvRecordListener
        Parameters:
        record - record object.
        supply - a Supply object representing the changes.
        isSnapshot - true if the current update is a snapshot.
        See Also:
        MkvRecord.getErrorCode()

      • onUnpublish

        void onUnpublish​(MkvRecord record)
        Event generated when a publication becomes unavailable.

        It is not safe, publishing new object during this notification.

        Parameters:
        record - the MkvRecord representing the publication.
